| location = [[Rocky View County]], {{AB}} {{CAN}} | nearest_city = [[Cochrane, Alberta|Cochrane]] | coordinates = {{coords|51|15|06|N|114|23|13|W|display=inline, title}} | area_km2 = 0.4 | established = | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | governing_body = [[Alberta Tourism, Parks and Recreation]] }}
'''Big Hill Springs Provincial Park''' is a [[provincial park]] in [[Alberta]], [[Canada]]. It is located {{convert|10|km|mi|abbr=on}} north of [[Cochrane, Alberta|Cochrane]], {{convert|6|km|mi|abbr=on}} from [[Alberta Highway 22|Highway 22]] on [[Alberta Highway 567|Highway 567]], in [[Rocky View County]].
Big Hill Springs is located northwest of [[Calgary]], [[Alberta]] at the foothills of the [[Rocky Mountains]]. The main attraction is a series of small waterfalls that flow year-round over rocky terraces covered with a lush growth of shrubs and grasses; the park is also the site of an historic fish hatchery and Alberta's first commercial creamery.
==Activities== Activities in the park include [[hiking]], scenic and [[wildlife]] viewing. A historic [[Hatchery|fish hatchery]] is also located in the park.
